<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{2}{x}-{3}{y}=-{16}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}+{6}{y}={40}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{1},{6}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{2}{x}+-{3}{y}=-{16}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{2}{x}=-{16}-{\left(-{3}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{-{16}-{\left(-{3}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{2}}}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{\left(\frac{{-{16}-{\left(-{3}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{2}}}}\right)}+{6}{y}={40}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{4}}{{-{{2}}}}\cdot{\left(-{16}\right)}--\frac{{4}}{{-{{2}}}}{\left(-{3}\right)}{y}+{6}{y}={40}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{32}-{\left({6}\right)}{y}+{6}{y}={40}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{y}+{\left({6}\right)}{y}={40}--{32}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{y}+{\left({6}\right)}{y}={72}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left({6}+{\left({6}\right)}\right)}{y}={72}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{12}{y}={72}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{72}}{{12}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={6}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{2}{x}+-{3}{\left({6}\right)}=-{16}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{2}{x}+{\left(-{18}\right)}=-{16}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{2}{x}=-{16}-{\left(-{18}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{2}{x}={2}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{2}}{{-{{2}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{1}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left(-{1},{6}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

